WEBVTT

00:00:01.501 --> 00:00:03.904
[cicadas chirping]

00:00:03.937 --> 00:00:05.373
<i>HIGURASHI: In elementary school,</i>

00:00:05.406 --> 00:00:08.008
<i>I had friends
just like everyone else.</i>

00:00:09.410 --> 00:00:11.712
<i>During summer break we'd all
get together</i>

00:00:11.745 --> 00:00:14.648
<i>and play at the public pool
every day until sunset.</i>

00:00:14.681 --> 00:00:15.983
[splashing]

00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:17.550
<i>Thinking back on it,</i>

00:00:17.584 --> 00:00:20.687
<i>my life peaked that summer
during elementary school.</i>

00:00:20.720 --> 00:00:22.022
[all laughing]

00:00:24.024 --> 00:00:25.859
<i>When it came time
for middle school,</i>

00:00:25.892 --> 00:00:30.130
<i>everyone began to notice I
was naturally an introvert.</i>

00:00:30.163 --> 00:00:32.866
<i>Before I knew it I was on
the outside looking in.</i>

00:00:32.899 --> 00:00:34.701
[rain pattering]

00:00:34.734 --> 00:00:36.937
<i>During my years in high school,</i>

00:00:36.971 --> 00:00:39.740
<i>I kept to myself
and spent my time reading</i>

00:00:39.773 --> 00:00:42.609
<i>and listening to rakugo stories.</i>

00:00:42.643 --> 00:00:44.812
<i>But in college I tried
to change myself.</i>

00:00:44.845 --> 00:00:48.215
<i>I did an overseas internship
and volunteer work.</i>

00:00:48.249 --> 00:00:51.218
<i>Hell, I even took
a personal development seminar.</i>

00:00:51.952 --> 00:00:53.554
<i>But what good was that?</i>

00:00:53.587 --> 00:00:55.989
<i>Everyone still saw me
as an empty, visionless,</i>

00:00:56.022 --> 00:00:57.725
<i>self-conscious idiot.</i>

00:00:57.758 --> 00:00:59.326
<i>To be fair, though,</i>

00:00:59.359 --> 00:01:02.396
<i>I really didn't know what
I wanted to do with myself.</i>

00:01:02.429 --> 00:01:05.099
KENCHO: For free.
AKIRA: What? Seriously?

00:01:05.132 --> 00:01:07.601
We gotta go!
I could eat three of those!

00:01:07.634 --> 00:01:10.137
- Do that and you'll just barf
'em up during practice.

00:01:10.170 --> 00:01:12.039
AKIRA: Nah, I'll be fine
this time.

00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:13.573
It's not gonna be
like last time.

00:01:13.607 --> 00:01:15.942
KENCHO: Wait, didn't you say
something like that before?

00:01:15.976 --> 00:01:17.211
AKIRA: Okay, but that
was like...

00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:19.246
<i>HIGURASHI: He should
have been like me:</i>

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:22.616
<i>empty, visionless,
and lacking ambition.</i>

00:01:22.649 --> 00:01:25.653
<i>Instead he just cruised
through life without</i>

00:01:25.686 --> 00:01:28.989
<i>a care in the world,
always enjoying himself,</i>

00:01:29.023 --> 00:01:30.590
<i>and that's why...</i>

00:01:30.858 --> 00:01:31.992
[grunts]

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.693
<i>I couldn't help but hate him</i>

00:01:33.727 --> 00:01:35.428
<i>so damn much!</i>

00:01:36.596 --> 00:01:40.233
Okay! Come out of there
and show yourself!

00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:43.237
Your dad's practically weeping
over here over what

00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:45.239
<i>a wonderful son he's got!</i>

00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:48.008
<i>AKIRA: I have to become
a zombie?</i>

00:01:48.041 --> 00:01:50.410
<i>Is that really the only way
to save my dad?</i>

00:01:50.911 --> 00:01:52.079
<i>What do I do?</i>

00:01:52.112 --> 00:01:53.514
<i>TERUO: Akira.</i>
[AKIRA gasps]

00:01:53.547 --> 00:01:55.716
<i>TERUO: Whatever you do,
do not open that door.</i>

00:01:55.749 --> 00:01:56.917
<i>[labored breathing]</i>

00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:58.953
[AKIRA shudders]
<i>TERUO: Listen to me.</i>

00:01:58.986 --> 00:02:01.321
The day you put your mom
in danger

00:02:01.355 --> 00:02:04.457
and make me watch my own kid
get eaten alive

00:02:04.491 --> 00:02:06.593
is the day we're no longer
a family.

00:02:06.626 --> 00:02:09.396
You got that?
So don't you dare come out!

00:02:09.429 --> 00:02:12.332
- But Dad!
If I don't do anything you'll--

00:02:12.366 --> 00:02:16.536
TERUO: Don't you worry about me,
Akira, please.

00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:20.474
The thing is I don't have a lot
of time left here as it is.

00:02:20.507 --> 00:02:21.641
[AKIRA gasps]

00:02:22.476 --> 00:02:23.978
Huh?

00:02:24.011 --> 00:02:25.412
AKIKO: It's true, Akira.

00:02:25.445 --> 00:02:27.348
Your father's got one
of those bad growths

00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:28.281
on his body,

00:02:28.315 --> 00:02:29.616
and with everything that's

00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:31.151
going on in the world right now,

00:02:31.184 --> 00:02:33.187
there's no doctors to treat him.

00:02:33.220 --> 00:02:35.589
AKIKO: He's running out of time.

00:02:35.623 --> 00:02:38.759
AKIRA: But you don't know that
for sure.

00:02:38.792 --> 00:02:41.628
If we search for a doctor
we might find one right away!

00:02:41.662 --> 00:02:43.230
And a vaccine to deal with

00:02:43.264 --> 00:02:44.831
the zombies could
be developed tomorrow

00:02:44.864 --> 00:02:46.633
for all we know!

00:02:46.666 --> 00:02:48.235
If this happens,

00:02:48.268 --> 00:02:51.171
I'll never get the chance
to repay him for everything.

00:02:51.805 --> 00:02:53.641
- Akira.

00:02:53.674 --> 00:02:55.008
<i>TERUO: Listen to me.</i>

00:02:55.042 --> 00:02:56.877
<i>Help humanity.</i>

00:02:56.910 --> 00:02:58.379
[all gasping]

00:02:58.412 --> 00:03:00.714
<i>TERUO: Do everything you can
for the world.</i>

00:03:00.747 --> 00:03:04.117
<i>Don't ever lie just
to gain something for yourself.</i>

00:03:04.151 --> 00:03:08.188
<i>Become someone who
can feel empathy for others.</i>

00:03:08.221 --> 00:03:13.326
You can give back to us even
if we're not here anymore.

00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:16.630
<i>TERUO: If I can sit up there
in Heaven and watch you live out</i>

00:03:16.663 --> 00:03:18.566
<i>a full life of your own,</i>

00:03:18.599 --> 00:03:20.667
then I would be happy.

00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.236
There's nothing that
would make me prouder, son.

00:03:23.971 --> 00:03:27.475
[AKIRA shuddering]

00:03:27.508 --> 00:03:30.144
- Have you ever dreamed
of seeing the Earth...

00:03:30.177 --> 00:03:31.812
Ever since I was a little kid...

00:03:31.846 --> 00:03:33.113
Good luck, boy.
It's been my dream...

00:03:33.146 --> 00:03:36.283
<i>[multiple voices speaking
at once]</i>

00:03:47.494 --> 00:03:49.363
[inhales sharply]

00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:51.665
[exhales]

00:03:51.698 --> 00:03:54.668
HIGURASHI: Looks like he's not
comin' out after all.

00:03:54.701 --> 00:03:55.936
[inhales]

00:03:55.969 --> 00:03:58.038
Then again I guess some
half dead old guy

00:03:58.072 --> 00:04:00.407
isn't much of a hostage,
now, is it?

00:04:01.675 --> 00:04:03.410
ZOMBIES: Hmm?

00:04:03.443 --> 00:04:04.645
- [gasps]

00:04:04.678 --> 00:04:07.614
[all groaning]

00:04:10.017 --> 00:04:12.086
- [gasps]
Huh?

00:04:12.119 --> 00:04:15.222
[zombies groaning]

00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:19.693
[AKIRA screams]

00:04:19.727 --> 00:04:21.061
[blows landing]

00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:23.230
- [gasping]

00:04:23.964 --> 00:04:26.433
[AKIRA groaning]

00:04:28.402 --> 00:04:31.338
- [cackling]

00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:34.574
- [whimpers]
Akira.

00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:35.843
You are a damn fool!

00:04:35.876 --> 00:04:37.478
- I did it!

00:04:37.511 --> 00:04:39.179
Finally!

00:04:39.212 --> 00:04:40.981
HIGURASHI: I turned
the person I hate more

00:04:41.015 --> 00:04:43.917
than anyone else into a zombie!

00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:46.219
Look at you now!
Look at you!

00:04:46.253 --> 00:04:48.289
And now that you're a zombie
I'll never have

00:04:48.322 --> 00:04:52.359
to see that dumb ass grin
on your face ever again!

00:04:52.393 --> 00:04:54.528
The fun times are over
for you now!

00:04:54.561 --> 00:04:55.429
You got that?

00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:57.732
You can't do what
you want anymore!

00:04:57.765 --> 00:04:59.766
I won!
I beat you!

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:01.168
- [groans]

00:05:01.202 --> 00:05:03.303
[snickers]
- [grunting]

00:05:09.610 --> 00:05:10.644
[HIGURASHI gasping]

00:05:10.677 --> 00:05:14.381
[stammering]

00:05:14.414 --> 00:05:16.583
HIGURASHI: What is this?
[whimpers]

00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:21.121
What the hell is going on?

00:05:21.155 --> 00:05:22.289
AKIRA: I'm sorry.

00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:23.190
all: Huh?

00:05:23.224 --> 00:05:25.125
- It's risky.
I have a plan,

00:05:25.159 --> 00:05:26.927
but I'm gonna need
everyone's help

00:05:26.961 --> 00:05:28.295
to pull it off.

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:29.296
- Huh?

00:05:30.364 --> 00:05:31.966
NAGISA: We'll deepen
your eye sockets,

00:05:31.999 --> 00:05:34.902
hollow out your cheeks,
and make some bruises.

00:05:34.935 --> 00:05:36.270
For the blood I'll make
it sticky

00:05:36.303 --> 00:05:38.338
by adding some
laundry detergent.

00:05:38.371 --> 00:05:41.542
For your teeth we use
a brown alcohol-based ink.

00:05:41.575 --> 00:05:44.244
And finally we'll give
you white contacts.

00:05:45.145 --> 00:05:47.047
[all gasping]
AKIRA: Wow!

00:05:47.081 --> 00:05:48.615
This is so awesome!

00:05:48.649 --> 00:05:51.018
I look just like a zombie!

00:05:51.051 --> 00:05:52.252
- Mm, mm!

00:05:53.854 --> 00:05:55.155
- [shudders]

00:05:55.189 --> 00:05:58.659
[zombies groaning]
[shouting]

00:05:58.692 --> 00:06:00.194
[zombies groaning]

00:06:00.227 --> 00:06:02.195
[blows landing]
[all grunting]

00:06:03.831 --> 00:06:06.166
[all exhaling sharply]

00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:08.902
- It's all you now, Akira.
Knock 'em dead.

00:06:08.936 --> 00:06:11.305
- Oh, yeah. I got this.
[chuckles]

00:06:11.338 --> 00:06:14.007
- [gasping]

00:06:14.041 --> 00:06:15.910
AKIRA: Sorry it took so long.
You okay?

00:06:15.943 --> 00:06:17.945
- I'm okay.
I'll be fine, son.

00:06:17.978 --> 00:06:19.846
I can still move,
after all.

00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:22.415
- [gasps]
Dammit.

00:06:23.483 --> 00:06:24.751
HIGURASHI: Dammit!

00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:28.022
AKIRA: Higurashi.

00:06:28.055 --> 00:06:29.756
What was the point of this?

00:06:29.789 --> 00:06:31.391
What did you wanna gain from it?

00:06:31.424 --> 00:06:33.360
HIGURASHI: The same thing
as you!

00:06:33.394 --> 00:06:36.530
I wanna do everything
and anything I wanted!

00:06:36.564 --> 00:06:39.166
Is it really that wrong for me
to have some fun

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:42.069
for once in my life?

00:06:42.102 --> 00:06:43.804
AKIRA: If this
is really what you wanted,

00:06:43.838 --> 00:06:46.273
if you wanted
to just enjoy yourself...

00:06:47.541 --> 00:06:48.876
Then why?

00:06:48.909 --> 00:06:50.911
Why didn't it look like you
were having fun?

00:06:50.944 --> 00:06:54.048
- [gasping]

00:06:54.081 --> 00:06:58.452
Of course I'm having fun!
This is exactly what I--

00:06:58.485 --> 00:07:01.488
<i>HIGURASHI: What I wanted
to do?</i>

00:07:01.521 --> 00:07:03.157
<i>AKIRA: Higurashi.
Higurashi!</i>

00:07:03.190 --> 00:07:04.291
- [gasps]
[zombie groaning]

00:07:04.324 --> 00:07:05.525
The hell?

00:07:05.559 --> 00:07:07.294
[zombie munching]

00:07:07.795 --> 00:07:09.663
Hey, stop.

00:07:09.697 --> 00:07:12.066
Ah, get off me!

00:07:12.099 --> 00:07:15.903
Dammit, dammit, dammit,
dammit, dammit!

00:07:15.936 --> 00:07:19.540
Dammit!

00:07:19.573 --> 00:07:22.743
[gasps]
God dammit!

00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.278
[crying]

00:07:24.311 --> 00:07:26.179
- We have to get going, Akira.

00:07:26.213 --> 00:07:28.115
The zombies will be here
any second.

00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:29.550
[all gasping]

00:07:29.583 --> 00:07:31.952
[zombies groaning]

00:07:31.985 --> 00:07:35.088
[HIGURASHI crying]

00:07:36.690 --> 00:07:38.525
- [inhales and exhales sharply]

00:07:38.558 --> 00:07:41.028
What's on your real list?

00:07:41.061 --> 00:07:43.229
AKIRA: What did you want
to write down

00:07:43.263 --> 00:07:45.866
in your real bucket list,
Higurashi?

00:07:45.899 --> 00:07:47.301
.[HIGURASHI gasps]

00:07:47.334 --> 00:07:49.703
I wanted...

00:07:49.736 --> 00:07:52.773
The thing I wanted more
than anything in the world...

00:07:52.806 --> 00:07:53.907
[gasps]
[cicadas chirping]

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:56.543
FRIEND A: Whoa,
the water's awesome!

00:07:56.576 --> 00:07:58.045
[all laughing]

00:07:58.078 --> 00:08:00.313
FRIEND B: Wow, so fast!
I guess I lost.

00:08:00.347 --> 00:08:03.483
HIGURASHI: All right!
Yeah!

00:08:05.419 --> 00:08:06.487
[HIGURASHI gasps]

00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:08.822
FRIEND A: Way to go overboard,
Higurashi.

00:08:08.855 --> 00:08:11.791
[all laughing]

00:08:17.998 --> 00:08:22.102
Only thing that I really
ever wanted to do was...

00:08:25.072 --> 00:08:28.442
To have fun playing
at the public pool

00:08:28.475 --> 00:08:29.943
with my friends.

00:08:29.977 --> 00:08:32.613
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:08:32.646 --> 00:08:36.216
- If that's true,
you're a fool, Higurashi.

00:08:37.317 --> 00:08:39.320
Yeah, but I can stomach it,

00:08:39.353 --> 00:08:41.821
'cause I haven't
had breakfast yet today!

00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:42.789
[KENCHO groans]

00:08:42.822 --> 00:08:45.759
[all laughing]

00:08:46.660 --> 00:08:48.228
all: Huh?

00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:50.797
- [stammering]

00:08:53.968 --> 00:08:56.403
- Hey, you're in
my Gen Ed program, right?

00:08:56.436 --> 00:08:57.938
If you're hungry
do you wanna come

00:08:57.972 --> 00:08:58.873
and eat with us right now?

00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:00.007
- [whimpers]

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.508
[gasping]

00:09:04.111 --> 00:09:05.279
- What's his deal?

00:09:05.312 --> 00:09:07.047
Why'd he run off like that?

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:09.282
- Eh, they're gonna run out.
Come on, let's go.

00:09:11.218 --> 00:09:14.054
<i>AKIRA: Back then,
you should have told us.</i>

00:09:16.089 --> 00:09:18.391
Maybe then it could
have ended up differently.

00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:22.062
[HIGURASHI crying]

00:09:22.095 --> 00:09:23.530
AKIRA: Listen.

00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:26.666
If the time comes when
I really become a zombie...

00:09:26.700 --> 00:09:30.103
Let's go to the pool
and play like it's summer, okay?

00:09:30.137 --> 00:09:32.672
[HIGURASHI wailing]

00:09:43.149 --> 00:09:44.584
[zombies groaning]
[all gasping]

00:09:46.486 --> 00:09:48.289
[HIGURASHI crying]

00:09:48.322 --> 00:09:49.389
[grunts]

00:09:53.493 --> 00:09:56.596
[zombies groaning]

00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:58.498
- [gasps]

00:09:59.266 --> 00:10:01.068
[inhales and exhales]

00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:03.170
Let's get going.

00:10:03.203 --> 00:10:06.172
[children breathing heavily]
[cicadas chirping]

00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:10.444
- [panting]
[zombies groaning]

00:10:10.478 --> 00:10:11.511
[breathing heavily]

00:10:11.545 --> 00:10:14.048
[labored panting]
[zombies groaning]

00:10:14.081 --> 00:10:17.851
[cicadas chirping]

00:10:17.885 --> 00:10:20.787
[HIGURASHI panting]

00:10:28.461 --> 00:10:30.564
[gasps]

00:10:31.699 --> 00:10:32.699
[shudders]

00:10:33.801 --> 00:10:35.536
[groans]

00:10:35.569 --> 00:10:36.570
[gasps]

00:10:36.603 --> 00:10:39.539
[cicadas chirping]

00:10:42.909 --> 00:10:44.110
[exhales]

00:10:45.946 --> 00:10:47.347
[chuckles]

00:10:49.616 --> 00:10:51.551
[water splashes]

00:10:55.622 --> 00:10:56.990
KENCHO: Hey!
all: Huh?

00:10:57.024 --> 00:10:58.158
KENCHO: Are you guys okay?

00:10:58.192 --> 00:10:59.760
What happened?
- [gasps]

00:10:59.794 --> 00:11:02.429
[groans]
Kencho, that you?

00:11:02.463 --> 00:11:05.432
- Akira?
Why are you a zombie right now?

00:11:05.466 --> 00:11:06.600
AKIRA: What stinks?
[retches]

00:11:06.633 --> 00:11:08.535
SHIZUKA: There you are.
You're all right.

00:11:08.568 --> 00:11:09.803
[all gasping]

00:11:09.837 --> 00:11:11.505
- I gathered everyone
from the village.

00:11:11.538 --> 00:11:12.539
[all gasping]

00:11:13.874 --> 00:11:14.975
AKIRA: This is bad.

00:11:15.008 --> 00:11:16.643
We gotta get outta here,
and fast!

00:11:16.677 --> 00:11:19.279
- Yeah, but how do we get past
this electric fence?

00:11:19.946 --> 00:11:21.548
- Here I come!

00:11:21.581 --> 00:11:23.050
Out of the way, please!

00:11:23.083 --> 00:11:24.284
[all gasping]

00:11:24.318 --> 00:11:25.452
KENCHO: Bea?
SHIZUKA: Beatrix?

00:11:25.486 --> 00:11:27.287
- I cannot seem
to get down from here

00:11:27.321 --> 00:11:30.057
so I'll just have to crash
this into the electric fence!

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:31.258
[all gasping]

00:11:31.292 --> 00:11:33.160
AKIRA: Everyone,
stand back from the fence

00:11:33.194 --> 00:11:34.561
and open up a path!

00:11:34.594 --> 00:11:36.596
KENCHO: All healthy bodies who
are able to,

00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:38.765
give the old folks a hand!
NAGISA: It's okay, I've got you.

00:11:38.799 --> 00:11:39.833
BEATRIX: Here I go!

00:11:39.867 --> 00:11:40.935
[electric sparking]

00:11:40.968 --> 00:11:42.102
- It's down!

00:11:42.135 --> 00:11:45.138
Make a run for it!

00:11:45.172 --> 00:11:48.275
[KENCHO breathing heavily]

00:11:49.009 --> 00:11:50.578
[all breathing heavily]

00:11:50.611 --> 00:11:51.978
[BEATRIX breathing heavily]

00:11:52.012 --> 00:11:53.948
[distant zombies groaning]

00:11:53.981 --> 00:11:56.450
- [breathing heavily]

00:11:56.483 --> 00:11:58.685
AKIRA: I see the suspension
bridge up ahead!

00:11:59.319 --> 00:12:02.289
[panting]

00:12:03.824 --> 00:12:05.826
[gasping

00:12:05.859 --> 00:12:07.694
[all gasping]

00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:09.296
- No way.

00:12:09.329 --> 00:12:10.764
AKIRA: The suspension bridge.

00:12:10.797 --> 00:12:13.233
SHIZUKA: That was our only way
of getting out of here.

00:12:14.001 --> 00:12:17.070
[zombies groaning]

00:12:19.439 --> 00:12:23.410
- [groans]
Damn! What do we do now?

00:12:23.444 --> 00:12:25.913
- [gasps]
KUMANO: Look alive over there!

00:12:25.946 --> 00:12:26.947
- [gasps]

00:12:26.980 --> 00:12:27.981
KUMANO: I got a feeling

00:12:28.014 --> 00:12:29.549
you're gonna need this!

00:12:29.583 --> 00:12:31.017
- Huh?
Whoa!

00:12:31.051 --> 00:12:33.754
[groaning]

00:12:33.787 --> 00:12:35.956
Oh, wow!
Mr. Kumano!

00:12:35.989 --> 00:12:37.591
AKIRA: You came for us!

00:12:37.624 --> 00:12:40.461
- I came to see what the zombies
were up in arms about,

00:12:40.494 --> 00:12:43.063
only to see your
suspension bridge gave out,

00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:45.866
so I built you a brand new one
in a jiffy!

00:12:45.900 --> 00:12:48.035
[cackling]

00:12:48.068 --> 00:12:49.769
I'm a man of my word.

00:12:49.803 --> 00:12:51.705
You fellas can always count
on me.

00:12:51.738 --> 00:12:53.807
- [snickers]

00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:56.143
[zombies groaning]
[all gasping]

00:12:56.176 --> 00:12:57.578
- They're almost on us!

00:12:57.611 --> 00:12:59.046
[AKIRA and KENCHO grunting]

00:12:59.079 --> 00:13:01.182
AKIRA: We'll hold up
the bridge for you guys!

00:13:01.215 --> 00:13:03.950
- Hurry up!
Get moving!

00:13:03.984 --> 00:13:05.986
[all screaming]

00:13:06.020 --> 00:13:07.921
[KENCHO grunts]
Hurry!

00:13:07.954 --> 00:13:10.591
AKIRA: Hurry!

00:13:10.624 --> 00:13:12.492
- Everyone's made it across!

00:13:13.827 --> 00:13:16.097
- [grunts]
You ready, Kencho?

00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:18.465
- You bet.
Let's go.

00:13:18.499 --> 00:13:19.666
[both grunting]

00:13:19.700 --> 00:13:24.437
[both shouting]

00:13:25.339 --> 00:13:29.276
This is--whoa--scary!
- Scary!

00:13:29.309 --> 00:13:30.544
[bangs]

00:13:33.546 --> 00:13:34.749
[both gasping]

00:13:34.782 --> 00:13:36.516
[both breathing heavily]

00:13:36.549 --> 00:13:37.517
[all gasping]

00:13:37.551 --> 00:13:39.119
[both whimpering]

00:13:39.152 --> 00:13:42.289
[wind howling]

00:13:44.624 --> 00:13:47.561
[both screaming]

00:13:48.428 --> 00:13:51.331
[all cheering]

00:13:51.999 --> 00:13:53.566
[both sighing in relief]

00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:55.268
[both giggling]

00:13:59.273 --> 00:14:02.542
KENCHO: So that's it?
He just wanted friends?

00:14:02.576 --> 00:14:06.046
If that really is all Higurashi
wanted out of life then

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:08.415
he's a goddamn fool.

00:14:08.448 --> 00:14:10.684
AKIRA: Yeah.

00:14:10.717 --> 00:14:14.021
But when I was working
for that exploitative company,

00:14:14.054 --> 00:14:16.056
I also lost sight of myself.

00:14:16.089 --> 00:14:18.625
Every day was so painful.

00:14:18.658 --> 00:14:22.362
I had no idea what I
was even living for anymore.

00:14:22.396 --> 00:14:24.698
If I had wanted
to make my own twisted list

00:14:24.731 --> 00:14:26.633
like his evil notebook,

00:14:26.667 --> 00:14:29.536
I easily could have.

00:14:29.569 --> 00:14:32.739
No, anyone could
have become like Higurashi.

00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:37.044
So despite everything,
even if I wanted to,

00:14:37.077 --> 00:14:38.778
I can't hate him
for the things he did.

00:14:40.914 --> 00:14:43.417
KENCHO: All right,
there we go.

00:14:43.450 --> 00:14:45.685
[AKIRA grunting]

00:14:46.453 --> 00:14:47.888
[gasps]

00:14:47.922 --> 00:14:50.591
TERUO: You did good back there,
Akira.

00:14:50.624 --> 00:14:53.727
Without you your mom
and everyone in the village

00:14:53.760 --> 00:14:55.262
wouldn't be here right now.

00:14:56.496 --> 00:15:00.300
Akira, I'm more than proud
to call you my son.

00:15:02.002 --> 00:15:03.436
[AKIRA laughs]

00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:07.541
So does that mean I was able
to repay you a little?

00:15:07.575 --> 00:15:10.477
[indistinct chatter]

00:15:16.550 --> 00:15:17.851
[fireworks popping]

00:15:17.884 --> 00:15:19.153
MALE VILLAGER A:
Now, seal it off!

00:15:19.186 --> 00:15:20.554
[zombies groaning]
[engines rumbling]

00:15:20.587 --> 00:15:22.322
MALE VILLAGER B: Are we sure
that's all the zombies?

00:15:22.355 --> 00:15:24.058
MALE VILLAGER C: We searched
every inch of the village.

00:15:24.091 --> 00:15:26.093
There's no mistaking it.

00:15:26.126 --> 00:15:29.296
[birds chirping]

00:15:29.330 --> 00:15:32.566
SHIZUKA: You're planning on
restarting here in the village?

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:35.269
TOME: Well, we've only
got one hometown.

00:15:35.302 --> 00:15:37.103
Where else would we go?

00:15:37.137 --> 00:15:39.506
Now that Mr. Kumano
has moved here

00:15:39.539 --> 00:15:42.309
and is leading the charge
to rebuild the village,

00:15:42.342 --> 00:15:44.812
everyone's peppier
than ever around here.

00:15:44.845 --> 00:15:48.248
It's almost like they've got
a second shot at life in 'em.

00:15:48.282 --> 00:15:51.618
I'm sure it won't be long before
the village is back to normal,

00:15:51.651 --> 00:15:53.353
especially with him in charge.

00:15:53.387 --> 00:15:55.122
- [grunts]

00:15:55.155 --> 00:15:56.890
TOME: It's all thanks to you,
Shizuka.

00:15:56.923 --> 00:15:58.425
- Huh?
- Oh, come on.

00:15:58.458 --> 00:16:00.927
You were our village doctor,
remember?

00:16:00.961 --> 00:16:04.631
SHIZUKA: Oh, not really.
I'm not even a doctor.

00:16:04.665 --> 00:16:07.468
TOME: What you did was cure us
old whiners when we were ready

00:16:07.501 --> 00:16:09.003
to give in.

00:16:09.036 --> 00:16:11.638
For that, dear,
I can't thank you enough.

00:16:11.671 --> 00:16:13.039
- [gasps]

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:15.376
[grunts]

00:16:15.409 --> 00:16:17.444
ANJU: Here, hold this.
[KENCHO exhales]

00:16:18.112 --> 00:16:20.246
[ANJU grunting]

00:16:20.280 --> 00:16:23.183
Hold it steady or we're
not gonna finish before dinner!

00:16:23.216 --> 00:16:24.784
KENCHO: Uh, right.

00:16:24.818 --> 00:16:27.120
[ANJU grunting]

00:16:27.154 --> 00:16:29.823
- Angie, you're like
an entirely different person.

00:16:29.856 --> 00:16:31.092
[ANJU grunts]

00:16:31.125 --> 00:16:33.493
Well, time isn't gonna repair
the fence.

00:16:33.527 --> 00:16:37.197
And besides, I don't wanna
just keep crying over zombies.

00:16:37.231 --> 00:16:38.966
ANJU: I was able
to move forward because

00:16:38.999 --> 00:16:40.901
a funny guy got me to smile.

00:16:40.934 --> 00:16:42.703
- Oh.

00:16:42.736 --> 00:16:45.472
- So thank you, Mr. Comedian.

00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:46.473
- [gasps]

00:16:46.507 --> 00:16:47.440
[chuckles]

00:16:54.114 --> 00:16:57.017
- [labored breathing]

00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:03.957
AKIKO: He's sound asleep,
isn't he?

00:17:03.990 --> 00:17:05.125
[AKIRA gasps]

00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:10.097
- It's because he's worn
himself ragged all of this time.

00:17:10.130 --> 00:17:14.434
AKIKO: Every day he never failed
to ask me the same thing:

00:17:14.467 --> 00:17:16.770
"Have we heard
from Akira lately?

00:17:16.803 --> 00:17:19.306
You think Akira
is doing all right?"

00:17:19.339 --> 00:17:21.642
AKIRA: Well, in a world full
of zombies,

00:17:21.675 --> 00:17:22.842
I guess even a curmudgeon

00:17:22.876 --> 00:17:24.478
like Dad would
be worried about me.

00:17:24.511 --> 00:17:26.113
AKIKO: Not like that.

00:17:26.146 --> 00:17:28.916
He started asking the day after
you left for Tokyo.

00:17:28.949 --> 00:17:31.551
- [gasps]

00:17:34.722 --> 00:17:37.624
- [labored breathing]

00:17:38.458 --> 00:17:39.627
AKIRA: If...

00:17:39.660 --> 00:17:42.997
[sniffling]

00:17:43.030 --> 00:17:44.298
AKIRA: Not to say that
it's going to,

00:17:44.331 --> 00:17:48.368
but if anything happens to you,
Dad,

00:17:48.401 --> 00:17:50.971
I promise that I'll always...

00:17:51.004 --> 00:17:53.541
I'll always keep Mom
and the village safe.

00:17:53.574 --> 00:17:55.943
I'll keep them safe even
if you're not here

00:17:55.976 --> 00:17:59.079
to do it, Dad.
[crying]

00:18:02.883 --> 00:18:04.585
<i>AKIRA: By the way,</i>

00:18:04.618 --> 00:18:06.520
<i>what does dad have?</i>

00:18:06.553 --> 00:18:09.457
[wind blowing]

00:18:09.490 --> 00:18:11.157
[groans]

00:18:11.191 --> 00:18:13.394
Hemorrhoids?
That's it? Seriously?

00:18:13.427 --> 00:18:15.062
- That's right.
[all groaning]

00:18:15.095 --> 00:18:18.031
It's true
and he can't stand hospitals

00:18:18.065 --> 00:18:20.500
so he hasn't done anything yet
to treat them.

00:18:20.533 --> 00:18:22.670
The bleeding's awful
and it's too painful for him

00:18:22.703 --> 00:18:24.070
to stand too long.

00:18:24.104 --> 00:18:27.073
AKIRA: Um, then why
is he wheezing so hard?

00:18:27.107 --> 00:18:29.877
AKIKO: Lately it's been very hot
in the countryside,

00:18:29.910 --> 00:18:31.078
even at night.

00:18:31.112 --> 00:18:33.481
It's difficult for us old timers
to sleep.

00:18:33.514 --> 00:18:36.249
- Still, we can't ignore
the hemorrhoids he has!

00:18:36.282 --> 00:18:38.552
If something like that
is left alone without treatment

00:18:38.586 --> 00:18:39.486
for too long it could lead

00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:41.555
to a life-threatening infection,
you know!

00:18:41.588 --> 00:18:45.091
[AKIRA laughing]

00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:47.561
I see.
It's just hemorrhoids, huh?

00:18:50.263 --> 00:18:52.766
TERUO: Find your dream, Akira.

00:18:52.799 --> 00:18:55.235
Find the biggest one you can.

00:18:55.268 --> 00:18:57.070
Your dreams keep a man solid.

00:18:57.104 --> 00:18:58.772
Don't ya ever forget that.

00:18:59.540 --> 00:19:01.541
- [chuckles]

00:19:01.575 --> 00:19:03.077
AKIRA: If that's the case,

00:19:03.110 --> 00:19:05.846
I think it's time I leave
the village.

00:19:05.879 --> 00:19:07.114
- Huh?

00:19:07.148 --> 00:19:09.116
- Huh?
- But they're still rebuilding.

00:19:09.150 --> 00:19:11.986
- Akira, what do you want
to do outside

00:19:12.019 --> 00:19:13.453
the village so badly?

00:19:13.487 --> 00:19:16.490
AKIRA: If what Shizuka said
was true and the zombies

00:19:16.523 --> 00:19:18.024
are caused by a virus...

00:19:19.793 --> 00:19:23.030
I'll travel the country
and look for a cure to it!

00:19:23.063 --> 00:19:24.832
Then I'll convince Dad
to get surgery

00:19:24.865 --> 00:19:26.901
for his hemorrhoids!
Yeah!

00:19:26.934 --> 00:19:28.502
- Ah?

00:19:28.535 --> 00:19:30.170
[all gasping]

00:19:30.203 --> 00:19:31.972
- "Do your best to help humanity

00:19:32.005 --> 00:19:33.574
and do what you can
for the world."

00:19:33.607 --> 00:19:36.042
Those were Dad's last wishes,
after all.

00:19:36.076 --> 00:19:37.978
both: He's still alive, though.

00:19:38.012 --> 00:19:40.480
TERUO: Going out to save
the world, huh?

00:19:40.514 --> 00:19:42.416
That's the wildest thing
I've heard.

00:19:42.449 --> 00:19:44.050
[all gasping]

00:19:44.084 --> 00:19:47.487
It's a mighty big dream,
though, and I like it!

00:19:56.730 --> 00:19:57.697
- [chuckles]

00:19:59.566 --> 00:20:01.502
AKIRA: How about you guys?
all: Hmm?

00:20:01.535 --> 00:20:04.437
Is there anything you wanna add
to the bucket list?

00:20:04.471 --> 00:20:05.538
- Hmm?
- Ah.

00:20:05.572 --> 00:20:08.909
[all chuckling]

00:20:08.942 --> 00:20:11.345
- Well, now that you ask,
here's one for me.

00:20:11.378 --> 00:20:13.414
I'm sure there are lots
of people across Japan

00:20:13.447 --> 00:20:15.849
who are crying just
like Angie was.

00:20:15.882 --> 00:20:17.384
- This time I wanna try

00:20:17.418 --> 00:20:19.185
and make my childhood dream
come true.

00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:22.188
- As of right now
I've only toured

00:20:22.222 --> 00:20:23.590
the zombie-infested parts
of Nippon.

00:20:25.693 --> 00:20:27.027
- Sounds great!

00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:28.262
Let's keep it up
and write down all

00:20:28.295 --> 00:20:30.331
the stuff we wanna do in Japan!
Let's go!

00:20:30.364 --> 00:20:32.099
- I wanna throw a party on
a cruise ship!

00:20:32.132 --> 00:20:33.934
- I wanna swim with dolphins!

00:20:33.967 --> 00:20:36.102
- I want to be able
to live in a castle!

00:20:36.136 --> 00:20:37.637
KENCHO: Meditate under
a waterfall!

00:20:37.671 --> 00:20:39.206
AKIRA: I wanna ride an ostrich!

00:20:39.240 --> 00:20:42.309
SHIZUKA: Ooh, I've always wanted
to eat Yoboku squid served live!

00:20:42.342 --> 00:20:43.877
BEATRIX: I want
to experience hatsumode

00:20:43.910 --> 00:20:45.279
at Ise Shrine!

00:20:45.312 --> 00:20:46.947
AKIRA: You can do that!
KENCHO: Ah, nice one!

00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:49.115
[all talking at once]

00:20:52.152 --> 00:20:53.486
MALE VILLAGER D:
Got enough water?

00:20:53.520 --> 00:20:55.355
MALE VILLAGER E: Oh,
and take some vegetables, too.

00:20:55.389 --> 00:20:57.524
TOME: It's just gonna get colder
from here on.

00:20:57.558 --> 00:20:59.826
Feel free
to take whatever you need.

00:20:59.860 --> 00:21:01.161
- Thank you so much.

00:21:01.194 --> 00:21:03.630
OLD MAN HIKO: Akemi?
TOME: Hmm?

00:21:03.663 --> 00:21:07.801
- I'll always be waiting here.
You come back now, you hear?

00:21:07.835 --> 00:21:09.837
- Old Man Hiko.

00:21:09.870 --> 00:21:12.740
I'm sorry but I'm not Akemi.

00:21:12.773 --> 00:21:14.374
I'm Shizuka.

00:21:18.378 --> 00:21:20.981
BEATRIX: It's going to be lonely
without him, isn't it?

00:21:21.014 --> 00:21:22.616
It's okay to cry, you know.

00:21:23.717 --> 00:21:25.685
Saying goodbye is never easy.

00:21:25.719 --> 00:21:28.221
He won't mind you shedding tears
in front of him.

00:21:29.456 --> 00:21:32.158
[ANJU crying]

00:21:32.192 --> 00:21:33.293
[BEATRIX gasps]

00:21:37.765 --> 00:21:38.765
[chuckles]

00:21:39.933 --> 00:21:41.335
ANJU: Mr. Kencho!

00:21:41.368 --> 00:21:43.236
KENCHO: Oh.

00:21:43.270 --> 00:21:45.305
- When you do get around
to coming back,

00:21:45.338 --> 00:21:47.742
show me how you slurp udon
with your butt!

00:21:47.775 --> 00:21:48.842
- Oh?

00:21:48.876 --> 00:21:50.076
Hah!

00:21:50.811 --> 00:21:52.312
AKIRA: Enough already!

00:21:52.345 --> 00:21:54.948
When are we gonna need all
this simmered seaweed?

00:21:54.982 --> 00:21:56.283
AKIKO: You never know,
so take it.

00:21:56.316 --> 00:21:58.118
It'll keep for some time.

00:21:58.151 --> 00:22:00.987
I don't like the idea
of you going hungry somewhere,

00:22:01.021 --> 00:22:03.657
so there's no such thing
as having too much food.

00:22:03.690 --> 00:22:05.225
- Thanks, Mom.

00:22:05.258 --> 00:22:06.927
TERUO: Akira.
- [whimpers]

00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:09.463
- Leave your mother to me, okay?

00:22:09.496 --> 00:22:10.731
- [gasps]

00:22:10.764 --> 00:22:11.731
[grunts]

00:22:15.302 --> 00:22:19.240
Okay, everyone.
I promise we'll be back...

00:22:19.273 --> 00:22:22.443
As soon as we're finished saving
the world!

00:22:22.476 --> 00:22:24.477
KENCHO: So,
what's the plan, Akira?

00:22:24.511 --> 00:22:26.513
We'll need a vaccine
to stop a virus.

00:22:26.547 --> 00:22:27.481
Isn't that right?

00:22:27.514 --> 00:22:29.249
- Are we heading
to an infectious disease

00:22:29.283 --> 00:22:31.652
research lab?
A US military base?

00:22:31.685 --> 00:22:33.453
AKIRA: Go north!
- Go north?

00:22:33.486 --> 00:22:36.289
- Hah, because all
good travelers venture north!

00:22:36.323 --> 00:22:38.759
I'm so excited
I can barely sit still!

00:22:38.792 --> 00:22:40.060
[all laughing]

00:22:40.093 --> 00:22:43.063
<i>[Kana-Boon's "Song of the Dead"]</i>

00:22:43.096 --> 00:22:46.033
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:46.066 --> 00:22:53.641
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:22:53.674 --> 00:22:54.675
<i>♪♪ Burger ♪♪</i>

00:22:54.708 --> 00:22:57.044
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:57.077 --> 00:22:59.446
<i>♪♪ Song of the dead,
song of the dead ♪♪</i>

00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:02.783
<i>♪♪ I wanna dancing, dancing
rolling, rolling ♪♪</i>

00:23:02.816 --> 00:23:04.952
<i>♪♪ Only one my life ♪♪</i>

00:23:04.985 --> 00:23:07.922
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:23:07.955 --> 00:23:10.758
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:10.791 --> 00:23:13.393
<i>♪♪ Da, da, da, dancing, dancing
morning, morning... ♪♪</i>

00:23:13.427 --> 00:23:16.864
- Is it only me or does it seem
like we're just sightseeing?

00:23:16.897 --> 00:23:19.666
It certainly doesn't seem like
we're searching for a solution.

00:23:19.699 --> 00:23:21.668
- It's all good.

00:23:22.769 --> 00:23:24.938
KENCHO: Hey, I think I see it!

00:23:24.972 --> 00:23:26.873
KENCHO: The Seikan Tunnel!

00:23:26.907 --> 00:23:28.042
<i>AKIRA: All right!</i>

00:23:28.075 --> 00:23:31.145
<i>Next up is Hokkaido!</i>

00:23:31.178 --> 00:23:33.981
- Sounds good to me!
[laughs]

00:23:34.014 --> 00:23:37.017
- [laughing]

00:23:37.050 --> 00:23:38.752
- [snickering]

00:23:39.820 --> 00:23:41.555
- [chuckles]

00:23:42.623 --> 00:23:44.724
- [laughs]

